# 🛡️ Linux Security Auditor 

A comprehensive Python tool that performs **45+ security checks** on Linux
systems and generates a detailed hardening report with a security score.

Built on Kali Linux for cybersecurity professionals, sysadmins, and
penetration testers.

---

## 🔥 Features

- **45+ automated security checks**
- **8 audit categories**
- Color-coded terminal output
- Security score with grade (0-100)
- JSON report export
- Fix suggestions for every issue found
- Rootkit & malware indicators detection
- Backdoor port scanning

---

## 📋 What It Checks

| Category | Checks |
|----------|--------|
| 👤 User & Auth | Root login, empty passwords, UID 0 users, password policy, sudo users |
| 🌐 Network | Firewall, open ports, IP forwarding, SYN cookies, ICMP redirects |
| 📂 File System | File permissions, SUID/SGID, world-writable files, unowned files |
| 🔑 SSH Hardening | 10 SSH settings including root login, key auth, X11, brute force |
| ⚙️ System & Kernel | Updates, ASLR, core dumps, dmesg, AppArmor/SELinux |
| 📝 Logging | rsyslog, auditd, log permissions, failed login attempts |
| 🦠 Malware | Suspicious cron jobs, hidden files, rootkit indicators, backdoor ports |
| 🔧 Services | Dangerous services, fail2ban status |

